  "formatted_phone_number": "01 42 34 56 10",
  "website": "https://www.notredamedeparis.fr/",
  "rating": 4.7,
  "reviews": [
    {
      "author_name": "Juan Manuel López Santana",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102688349196498977016/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWEuQrBLe4PFg7bsu1GPvN3A_hwXTxdvXV_YQu6L-3uI_jaYF4=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "2 weeks ago",
      "text": "What an amazing symbol of Gothic architecture! This is one of the oldest Gothic cathedrals. It's located at the downtown of the beautiful city of Paris.\n\nThe building is very popular, so probably when you visit it, you'll see a lot of people around.\n\nOne of the coolest things you can do is, to move around the  Sena river near the shore, where you can find some seats to admire the cathedral. I did it and it's a great experience!\n\nIt is a must, if you are visiting Paris. Definitely, don't skip this of your list.",
      "time": 1756917438,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Graham Hutchison",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114941084148809991830/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVHNncbDHjhUl6CWALWD-b--xWNH77qQ__A6JmIBAvzlr7h-gYu=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "2 weeks ago",
      "text": "Wonderful to see the restored splendour of this magnificent cathedral after the awful fire of 2019.  Free to enter, long queue but moved quickly and only took about 20 minutes to get inside.  There was a mass taking place when we visited so it was very busy inside but it was lovely to hear the organ music and singing showcasing the wonderful acoustics.  I would recommend timing your visit to coincidence with a service as this is an experience not to be missed.  The artwork and stained glass are exquisite and you have a real sense of history as you walk round this remarkable building which had played such an central part in the story of the French nation.",
      "time": 1757064813,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "M R",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108955353036896875224/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWTu3lkygecgAvtACtXXBO6vvp2ZqzcBd_nHEL-uC2TMXS2hTy5=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "a week ago",
      "text": "Iconic cathedral, so well known, no review is needed.  It continues to be restored by artisans and workers who are preserving and restoring the structure to inspire people for generations.  Expect scaffolding to still be around the outside structure for another few years.  The inside is gorgeous and looks as good or better than it has in 900 years.  The walk-up lines move pretty quickly and the tours are worth it.  Bathrooms are not available on site.  Pay toilets are nearby.",
      "time": 1757586835,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Brittney Conway",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116799845060157917490/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXrAMKOS87r_EdkHOao8dXvY3Ex9eBBTlEcz_Wzhrw1nnWsuv7ZBA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "a week ago",
      "text": "You do not need a ticket to enter! There are tour companies selling tickets but honestly, get in the line (looks super long but moves super fast - it’s basically a continuous loop in, around, and out) and check out this iconic cathedral. Even if you’re not catholic or religious, you can appreciate the beauty and wonder in awe how it was built. It’s still under construction on the outside from the fire, but inside it’s great.",
      "time": 1757782076,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "J Youde",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110888392815502405098/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIvu1sYixgQg6v56ggvodjgW3nCzFb7y5b0W880piNPDd8YrA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "in the last week",
      "text": "A must see place when visiting Paris! It’s free to get in and you don’t need to get any tickets in advance. During the busy season it’s best to get there early. We arrived at 8.45am and we walked straight in. It was still fairly quiet when we left at 10am.",
      "time": 1758038204,
      "translated": false
    }
