{"type":"text","text":"{
  "name": "Panthéon",
  "formatted_address": "Pl. du Panthéon, 75005 Paris, France",
  "location": {
    "lat": 48.8462218,
    "lng": 2.3464138
  },
  "website": "https://www.paris-pantheon.fr/",
  "rating": 4.6,
  "reviews": [
    {
      "author_name": "John Abrahamson",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110242012295636893027/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUPtm3fAG__B1l-zrEC2Mc_m0ltuH2gRDllr7V0ydyWe-4EkFTy8A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba8",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "2 weeks ago",
      "text": "Sizable place. Beautiful building. I liked how there were multiple themes going on with the art. (Christianity, Genevieve, etc) The crypt is interesting because there are many famous/important historical figures in there. But all the crypts are the same/redone. The rooftop was closed.on my day.",
      "time": 1756754031,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Sebahat Kaçar",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105521470722270886854/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV6aUsn3UV9bVx2xU3ERUo-1dpGBtzKAAFtOlRabBAE3YmsYs0=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "a week ago",
      "text": "The Panthéon was truly impressive. It wasn’t crowded, which made the visit very enjoyable. Inside, it’s fascinating to see the tombs of great figures like Victor Hugo, Voltaire, Rousseau, and Marie Curie. The grand dome and frescoes are breathtaking, and Foucault’s Pendulum is a highlight – a simple yet powerful demonstration of Earth’s rotation. Unfortunately, the terrace was temporarily closed – I would have loved to see the Paris view from there. Overall, a peaceful and historic site, definitely worth a visit.",
      "time": 1757259600,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Chris Oh! Boylesque",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109351158112901398069/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXeHKgTy736503mXGzXE5ptnxyJvMAHJw3do7HuRUqHOuqgH8aTdg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "3 weeks ago",
      "text": "Just beautiful! The murals on the walls are exceptional, the space awe inspiring, and the tombs a sobering reminder of some of the great people that helped form the French identity.\n\nIt truly was a special experience, informative, and a nice pause from the hustle and bustle of the city.",
      "time": 1756136335,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Benjamin Bodo",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116367812084302762917/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV8S2q7cNEdojtftVQplwrpH4EHW5p703etwgwBWqtRh-szKTI=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2",
      "rating": 4,
      "relative_time_description": "2 weeks ago",
      "text": "We arrived half an hour before closing and we were unable to enter. But the intricate architecture and design took us away into another world itself. This is yet another amazing and wonderful place to visit.",
      "time": 1756912369,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "A Karasahin",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114672075260701936921/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI0HMA_Y6PfbmFcs_AgEcG08dD5xSJSgD4YO8_nU1nILyE_xuY=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "a month ago",
      "text": "I saw the Pantheon from the outside, and sat there for some time in the square in front of it. You can catch a beautiful glimpse of the Eiffel Tower and the cityscape. I was there on a windy afternoon, so your experience may vary, but I had a really calm and peaceful pause here before moving onto the more bustling streets of Paris🗼",
      "time": 1755671307,
      "translated": false
    }
  ],
