  "rating": 4.8,
  "reviews": [
    {
      "author_name": "John Abrahamson",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110242012295636893027/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUPtm3fAG__B1l-zrEC2Mc_m0ltuH2gRDllr7V0ydyWe-4EkFTy8A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba8",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "2 weeks ago",
      "text": "Nice collection of art. Very affordable/fair prices compared to many other museums and galleries. The collection wasn't as large as I imagined, especially being such a large building. But it's worth a visit. There are some great photo opportunities from above, and the impressionists art is fantastic.",
      "time": 1756931548,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Sivatharjini Sivarajasingam",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111973848578790989035/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJMUmbX_Qu152VwNhcOuVHpxWVnOwVHEQH01FtSEY_Hvff9Iw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "in the last week",
      "text": "This place is honestly incredible! Due to limited time I focused on my personal favourite - Impressionists but you could easily spend a whole day here. The building itself it stunning.\n\nWould recommend going out of peak season, I visited in August and it was very busy. I wonder how it would feel with less hustle and bustle.\n\nA memorable part of my trip to Paris!\n\nAlso there is a queue for tickets to be bought on the day. It was swift (5-10mins) and easy.",
      "time": 1758011025,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Ivan Tan",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117991758272607395005/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVQN1wJ5Ewsincc-Xu-JNLsgh6U1zdgI6-dyxiQ-9Wo-2GDD_dB=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "2 months ago",
      "text": "I'm using Paris Museum Pass, just join the line via Entrance C.\n\nThis is one of the coolest art museums in Paris, it’s a must-visit if you’re Van Gogh's fan or simply into art. What makes it really special is that the building itself used to be a huge train station, it was the Gare d’Orsay, built around the early 1900s. Instead of tearing it down, they turned it into a museum, which means you get this amazing mix of old industrial architecture and art all in one place.\n\nInside, the museum is packed with incredible artworks, mostly from the late 19th and early 20th centuries. You’ll find tons of famous Impressionist and Post-Impressionist paintings here, artists like Monet, Degas, Renoir, Van Gogh, and Cézanne. If you love those bright, colorful paintings or want to get a feel for the art that changed the world, this is the spot.\n\nBesides paintings, the museum also has sculptures, decorative arts, and photography. It’s pretty manageable in size, so you don’t get overwhelmed like in some bigger museums.\n\nThe museum sits right on the left bank of the Seine, close to the Louvre and the charming Saint-Germain area. So, it’s easy to fit it into a day of exploring Paris.\n\nIt's recommended to visit here. :)",
      "time": 1750956479,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Thomas Wohl",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112321159397515173572/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWL6a4l56x2Ql6IjZYgQsOKHIcZejD9z3xQWhUD_jRhqqWUOwfnfg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "a month ago",
      "text": "Everybody knows how fantastic these places. The museum itself is just simply fantastic.  Well organized and clean easy to get around. Advice: get Timed Tickets otherwise  lines are really long. Audio guide well worth a little extra to learn about the paintings. Many different spots to take photos.\n\nThe card can get very big around famous artists and pictures.\n\n5 start!! Bring comfortable shoes :-)",
      "time": 1754999475,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Madalayne Rockarts",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112239832500819238746/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVPgkoVwgSwxCxjwOoqwj1qkROb_KqBCZmcwECJFCr2sCGIauNo5g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "2 weeks ago",
      "text": "Great museum to learn about art history and see a great variety of artwork and paintings! I would recommend checking this out.\n\nOnly downside is how busy it was which made it difficult to navigate. For popular artwork (like the van Gogh exhibit), we had to wait to see some paintings while groups of people took their photos and cycled through.",
      "time": 1757019404,
