{"type":"text","text":"{
  "name": "Musée de l'Orangerie",
  "formatted_address": "Jardin des Tuileries, 75001 Paris, France",
  "location": {
    "lat": 48.8637884,
    "lng": 2.3226724
  },
  "formatted_phone_number": "01 44 50 43 00",
  "website": "https://www.musee-orangerie.fr/fr",
  "rating": 4.6,
  "reviews": [
    {
      "author_name": "Kit Jan",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117806965578521652952/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWRWM33yj1rJMM_i3-veyf5b7m_eMBY0chwfaUjHRdrSyDrXfd2=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "a month ago",
      "text": "I can’t put into words how incredible this museum was!\nI came specifically to see Monet’s work, and it truly blew me away — so serene and moving.\n\nEven if you’re not usually into art, I’d still highly recommend a visit. The atmosphere is calming, and there’s something for everyone. They even have a children’s activity area, which is a lovely touch for families, as well as a few other types of art exhibitions beyond Impressionism.",
      "time": 1754120015,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Tony Dani",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106255627531491328781/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW7nTXugpxJaQm6cnAuekl_LoSEdt4eKOVfxk4hCLsMN1D9ygEIaQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "in the last week",
      "text": "Wonderful smallish museum in Paris. The building was especially designed to showcase Claude Monet's large impressionist paintings from his estate in Giverny. They were painted to be shown on the curved walls. The design takes full advantage of the natural lighting. The lower galleries showcase various French artists so the exhibitions will change.",
