      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Coral Courtney",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113038228140400782495/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1CS1IiWTl2YhtvtoT4oRSBjCLpYrLkq2AEK4VydnI_VIpcWomvA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5",
      "rating": 4,
      "relative_time_description": "in the last week",
      "text": "There are eight canvases for Monet's water lilies. There is a collection of art in the basement which was primarily not to my taste. There is also a kids activity room and a fairly decent toilet and water bottle filling station. This place was a little bit challenging to get to by cab - but once you're in the park, it's quite pleasant to walk around. I spent about 15 minutes in line with pre-purchased timed entry tickets but once the line started to move I was ushered in quickly. There is an x-ray for your bag and you have to step through a metal detector. Past the initial desk is the pickup for the audio guides on your right hand side. Present your tickets to the attendant to receive clean set. I'm not sure I would recommend the audio guide, although it did let me know about the second room of Monet, which would have been heartbreaking to find out later. There are quite a few stairs, although no full case to get to the Monet. Although to get to the yard downstairs and the family room, you do need to be able to do a full staircase.",
      "time": 1757880807,
      "translated": false
